<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-30] should allow receiving secure cookies from non-secure chanel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-30</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>Currently, httpclient will throw an exception if a secure cookie is received &lt;br/&gt;
from a non-secure chanel. Although RFC doesn&amp;#39;t specify explicitly on if the &lt;br/&gt;
client should allow receiving secure cookie from non-secure channel, the &lt;br/&gt;
default setting in browser seems to allow it.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Try the following link in IE:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.snapfish.com&quot;&gt;http://www.snapfish.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The default cookie policy in httpclient should be the same.</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other</environment>
