                    <comment id="12379278" author="marc.saegesser@apropos.com" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2002 03:03:33 +0100"  >RFC 2109 does not prohibit receiving secure cookies over and insecure channel &lt;br/&gt;
(See section 4.2.2).  Thus, HttpClient should not throw an an exception in this &lt;br/&gt;
case.  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The specification *does* gives us (the client) the leeway to decided when we &lt;br/&gt;
will send &amp;#39;secure&amp;#39; cookies back to the origin server.  HttpClient will sill &lt;br/&gt;
only add secure cookies to a Cookie header if the connection is secure.</comment>
